        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 6:05PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 605 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southeast of Lela, or 4 miles southwest of Shamrock, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shamrock, Lela, and Twitty.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
